    "recommended_approach": "Four-phase plan over 12 months, sequenced by severity and ROI. PHASE 0 (Week 1-2, EMERGENCY): Expand disk to 1TB+. Add index on orders(customer_id, created_at DESC). Add index supporting delivery history aggregation. Verify with EXPLAIN ANALYZE. Set up disk/CPU/latency monitoring alerts. PHASE 1 (Month 1-3): Deploy read replica. Route order search and delivery aggregation queries to replica. Deploy PgBouncer for connection pooling. Implement table partitioning on orders by month. Create materialized view for delivery history aggregations. PHASE 2 (Month 4-6): Scale API tier to 6-8 instances behind load balancer. Archive partitions older than 6 months to cold storage. Evaluate whether search index (ElasticSearch) is needed based on query patterns. Add second read replica if first is CPU-saturated. PHASE 3 (Month 7-12): Implement data retention/archival policy. Consider CQRS if read and write models have diverged. Evaluate vertical scaling of primary (larger instance class). Plan for 1M+ orders/day architecture if growth sustains (this would warrant revisiting sharding or NewSQL).",
