      "DO NOT partition the orders table without first verifying all queries include the partition key (created_at) — queries without it will scan ALL partitions and perform worse",
      "DO NOT scale API instances beyond 6 without PgBouncer — connection exhaustion will cause intermittent failures that are hard to diagnose",
      "DO NOT attempt sharding at current or 12-month projected volumes — it is premature and will consume the entire team for months",
      "DO NOT run CREATE INDEX without CONCURRENTLY on production — it will lock the table and cause an outage",
      "DO NOT skip monitoring setup — flying blind into 9x growth is how outages happen"
    ]
  },

  "escalations": [],

  "confidence": {
    "level": 82,
    "high_confidence_areas": [
      "Disk exhaustion timeline and mitigation — arithmetic is clear, this is urgent",
      "Missing indexes as root cause of slow queries — full table scan on order search is a textbook fix",
      "Read replica strategy — well-established pattern, PostgreSQL native, low risk",
      "Team bandwidth as binding constraint — 4 engineers cannot run parallel infrastructure projects"
    ],
    "low_confidence_areas": [
      "Exact CPU headroom gained from query optimization — depends on query mix and data distribution; estimated 30-40% reduction but needs measurement",
      "Whether growth rate sustains at 20% MoM for 12 months — if it accelerates, Phase 3 timeline compresses; if it slows, Phase 2/3 may be unnecessary",
      "Delivery history aggregation query structure — without seeing the actual query and schema, materialized view design is directional",
      "Partition migration complexity — depends on foreign key constraints, application ORM behavior, and existing query patterns"
    ],
    "assumptions": [
      "20% MoM growth rate is sustained, yielding ~445k orders/day at month 12 (~5.2 orders/second average, ~15/second peak)",
      "Data volume grows roughly proportionally to order volume",
      "The two identified slow queries (order search by customer, delivery aggregation) account for a significant share of DB CPU",
      "PostgreSQL is appropriately configured (shared_buffers, work_mem, effective_cache_size) — if not, tuning alone could yield 15-20% CPU reduction",
      "No hard latency SLA below 100ms P99 — current P99 of 800ms suggests this is already degraded beyond acceptable levels",
      "Budget exists for infrastructure scaling (larger disks, read replica instances, PgBouncer)"
    ]
  }
}

